To make sure I understand correctly, are you suggesting that ideally
link relations would specify (in the link registry) which method
should be used to navigate to the target URI? So perhaps a &quot;create&quot;
relation could be registered that specifies &quot;POST&quot; as the method to
use? Would this be problematic for custom relations that the client
may not be aware of the appropriate method for? Currently, the Atom
link registry does not specify any defined methods for any of the
existing relations that are registered. Even the &quot;edit&quot; relation
doesn&#39;t specify a method, it is still just GETable resource that one
can apply the uniform interface to.

